Yeah.

15:52.208 --> 15:53.667
Uh, well, as fun as this was,

15:53.750 --> 15:55.250
maybe we should
start heading back?

15:55.333 --> 15:57.458
I think Edie's probably ready
to check out the water.

15:57.542 --> 15:59.625
Oh, yeah, but Adriana
is<i> definitely </i>

15:59.709 --> 16:01.667
ready to check out the water.

16:03.000 --> 16:04.959
It's all right
if you want to stay.

16:05.041 --> 16:07.000
No, it's...
I don't<i> want </i>to stay.

16:07.083 --> 16:08.500
I<i> have </i>to stay.

16:08.583 --> 16:10.625
I'm refereeing a chicken fight.

16:10.709 --> 16:12.583
Great! Stay.
Yeah, ref the chicken fight.

16:12.667 --> 16:15.333
I'm gonna go play with
your granddaughter in the ocean.

16:15.417 --> 16:16.917
What, you mad at me?

16:17.000 --> 16:19.417
Come on, I put in real
time to your family day.

16:19.500 --> 16:21.333
I thought it was
<i>our </i>family day.

16:21.417 --> 16:25.125
You-you have spent this entire
day being embarrassed by us.

16:25.208 --> 16:27.583
Do you think I feel cool
singing "This Old Man"

16:27.667 --> 16:29.417
500 times in my mom's hatchback?

16:29.500 --> 16:31.250
Do you think
I like keeping track

16:31.333 --> 16:32.750
of how many baby wipes we have?

16:32.834 --> 16:34.750
I know I look like a dork
in this hat,

16:34.834 --> 16:37.208
but I have to wear it
because my daughter loves

16:37.291 --> 16:39.250
building sand castles,
but she sucks at it,

16:39.333 --> 16:42.250
and so, it takes forever,
and I get sunburned.

16:42.333 --> 16:45.458
You know, family is an endless
stream of just exhausting crap

16:45.542 --> 16:47.959
that makes you feel like
the least cool person on earth,

16:48.041 --> 16:50.500
but... but you do it
because you love your kid.

16:50.583 --> 16:53.291
I mean, 'cause sometimes,
you get these amazing moments,

16:53.375 --> 16:55.959
like watching her go
in the ocean for the first time.

16:56.041 --> 16:58.333
Which I'm not gonna miss
just explaining this to you.

16:58.417 --> 17:00.333
Okay, I get it.
Let's go back.

17:00.417 --> 17:02.333
Just stay, all right?
You don't have to do

17:02.417 --> 17:03.583
anything you don't want to do.

17:03.667 --> 17:05.291
That's the beauty
of this thing, right?

17:05.375 --> 17:06.709
We're adults. I'm 25.

17:06.792 --> 17:08.500
I'm 25 and a half.

17:08.583 --> 17:10.208
No one uses the fraction.

17:11.583 --> 17:13.083
Look, just stay, okay?

17:13.166 --> 17:14.667
